Dec 9 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines * BP fails in U.S. Supreme Court gulf appeal (http://on.ft.com/1D0GJ7C)  * Superbug threat drives $9.5 bln Merck deal (http://on.ft.com/1s5kuJ8)  * Canary Wharf shareholder agrees to sell stake as battle heats up (http://on.ft.com/1yu7sGP)  * U.S. sues Deutsche Bank in $190 mln taxes claim (http://on.ft.com/1s5lk8J)  * PwC sold 'tax avoidance on industrial scale' (http://on.ft.com/1Bur4f0)  Overview * The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday rejected BP's <BP.L> challenge to its multibillion dollar settlement agreement over the 2010 Gulf of Mexico oil spill, which the oil company complained has allowed unjustified payouts.  * Merck & Co Inc <MRK.N> said it would buy Cubist Pharmaceuticals Inc <CBST.O> for $8.4 billion plus assumption of debt, giving the major drugmaker an entry into the market for drugs that combat superbugs.  * Songbird Estates <SBDE.L> shareholder Madison International Realty has accepted Qatar Investment Authority and U.S. investor Brookfield Property Partners <BPY.N> 350 pence per share offer for the British property company.  * The U.S. government on Monday sued Deutsche Bank AG <DBKGn.DE>, seeking to recoup more than $190 million from the German bank over alleged tax fraud more than 14 years ago.